      r.pattern‚Üźsp‚ÜďmethodPath       ‚ćĚ '/items/{item_id}', ‚Ä¶
      r.handler‚Üźhandler             ‚ćĚ string; resolved against Handlers at call time
      _routes,‚Üź‚äār
    ‚ąá


    ‚ćĚ _MatchPath  ‚Äď  compare a pattern against an incoming URL
    ‚ćĚ   Right : (pattern path)
    ‚ćĚ   Result: (matched pathParams)
    ‚ćĚ
    ‚ćĚ Segments like {item_id} capture the corresponding URL segment.
    ‚ćĚ Captured values land on req.PathParams as character-vector fields.
    ‚ąá (matched pathParams)‚Üź_MatchPath(pattern path);patSegs;pathSegs;i;seg;name;val
      pathParams‚Üź‚éēNS ''
      matched‚Üź0
      patSegs‚Üź(pattern‚Č†'/')‚äÜpattern
      pathSegs‚Üź(path‚Č†'/')‚äÜpath
      :If (‚ćīpatSegs)‚Č†‚ćīpathSegs ‚čĄ :Return ‚čĄ :EndIf
      :For i :In ‚ć≥‚ćīpatSegs
          seg‚Üź‚äÉpatSegs[i]
          :If '{'=‚äÉseg                           ‚ćĚ named parameter
              name‚Üź1‚Üď¬Į1‚Üďseg                      ‚ćĚ strip { }
              val‚Üź‚äÉpathSegs[i]
              pathParams ‚éēVSET ‚äāname val         ‚ćĚ pathParams.name ‚Üź 'val'
          :ElseIf seg‚ČĘ‚äÉpathSegs[i]               ‚ćĚ literal mismatch ‚Üí no match
              :Return
          :EndIf
      :EndFor
      matched‚Üź1
    ‚ąá


    ‚ćĚ route an incoming Jarvis request to a handler
    ‚ąá result‚Üź_Dispatch req;routes;r;matched;pp
      :Access Public Instance    ‚ćĚ Public so closures in Start can call it
     
      routes‚Üź((‚éēc¬®_routes.method)‚ąä‚äā‚éēc req.Method)/_routes
      :For r :In routes
          (matched pp)‚Üź_MatchPath r.pattern req.Endpoint
          :If matched
              req.PathParams‚Üźpp
              req.QueryParams‚Üź(ns‚Üź‚éēNS '')‚éēVSET ‚Üďreq.QueryParams
              result‚Üź(Handlers ‚ćér.handler) req    ‚ćĚ look up fn by name, then call
              :Return
          :EndIf                                            

      :EndFor
      req.Fail 404
      result‚Üź‚éēNS ''
      result.detail‚Üź'Not Found'
    ‚ąá

:EndClass
